<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5019> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5019" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Governor (title not preserved) of Bithynia and Pontus (Head, HN² 497, 510, 516-518, coins of Amisus, Nicaea, and Nicomedia, dated in the years 222-224 of the Bithynian era)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4977> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4977" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Governor of Bithynia and Pontus (Head, HN² 497, 510, 516-518). See 61, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4948> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4948" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Governor of Bithynia and Pontus. Named without title on coins of Amisus (Head, HN² 497), Apameia, Myrleia, Nicaea, and Nicomedia (ib. 516-518). See Dio 36.40.3-4; Val. Max. 5.4.4, with praenomen Gn." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4894> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4894" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 61, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4694> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4694" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He received the consular insignia, in or soon after 67, as a reward for securing the conviction of M. Aurelius Cotta for misappropriation of the booty of Heracleia Pontica (Dio 36.40.3-4; cf. Val. Max. 5.4.4; Menmon 60, in FGrH 3B.358; see 73-70, Promagistrates, on Cotta)." .
